data.name: Spicy Sriracha Mayo
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and spicy condiment perfect for sandwiches, burgers, and dipping.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, combine 1 cup of mayonnaise with 2-3 tablespoons of Sriracha sauce.
Add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon of garlic powder.
Mix well until all ingredients are thoroughly combined and the sauce is a uniform color.
Taste and adjust the Sriracha for desired spice level.
Serve immediately or refrigerate for up to one week.
